\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3}{\ignorespaces \ref  {sub@fig:lauvs} Multiple Light Autonomous Underwater Vehicles such as the one shown above, were used in {\textbf  {FRESNEL}}. This low-cost platform designed at the University of Porto has demonstrated its robustness and integrates with a number of oceanographic sensors and comes with a sizable open source command/control software. \ref  {sub@fig:scheme} Three-day sequence (29\textsuperscript  {th} - 31\textsuperscript  {st} October 2024) of the \emph  {sample-–assimilate–-predict-–direct} loop in the {\textbf  {FRESNEL\ }}experiment. Each cycle integrated statistical model predictions using the {\color  {blue}{\{R1: CMEMS\}}} model as a prior, targeted sampling, AUV data acquisition, and subsequent assimilation for the following day's predict.\relax }}{9}{figure.caption.7}}
