\newlabel{fig:scatter}{{5}{15}{Comparison between in-situ AUV temperature ($^{\circ }$C) observations (31\textsuperscript {st} October) and model temperature ($^{\circ }$C) predictions for scenarios \textbf {C} \subref {fig:scatter_c}, \textbf {C4} (\subref {fig:scatter_c4}), \textbf {D} (\subref {fig:scatter_d}), and \textbf {D4} (\subref {fig:scatter_d4}). Shallower layers are shown in warmer colors (red to yellow), while deeper layers ($>$ 30m) are progressively represented in cooler shades (green to blue). The dashed red line provides a reference for correlation.\relax }{figure.caption.11}{}}
