\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {7}{\ignorespaces Temperature distributions from {\color  {blue}{\{R1: CMEMS\}}} for the northern and southern regions of the study area between the 18\textsuperscript  {th} and 31\textsuperscript  {th} October. The division between regions follows the line boundary shown in the inset map, top right. Only grid points shallower than 200m were retained to avoid including the canyon interface. Boxplots show the spatial distribution of {\color  {blue}{\{R1: CMEMS\}}} temperature within each region, capturing both the median and the spread of variability.\relax }}{18}{figure.caption.13}}
\newlabel{fig:north_south}{{7}{18}{Temperature distributions from \rone {CMEMS} for the northern and southern regions of the study area between the 18\textsuperscript {th} and 31\textsuperscript {th} October. The division between regions follows the line boundary shown in the inset map, top right. Only grid points shallower than 200m were retained to avoid including the canyon interface. Boxplots show the spatial distribution of \rone {CMEMS} temperature within each region, capturing both the median and the spread of variability.\relax }{figure.caption.13}{}}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {8}{\ignorespaces Trajectory of XP5 AUV, during the 30\textsuperscript  {th} October mission in the {Nazar\'{e}\ }Canyon region. The color shading represents the interquartile range (IQD) of temperature values recorded within each model grid cell illustrating the horizontal resolution of the statistical model. Results are shown for three representative depth layers: near-surface, 20 m, and 40 m, capturing distinct vertical regimes. Higher IQD values indicate regions of higher thermal variability within the model grid. Close-up view of the 20 m layer reveal fine-scale fluctuations occurring inside single grid elements illustrating AUVs capture subgrid-scale structure that the model does not resolve.\relax }}{18}{figure.caption.14}}
\newlabel{fig:iqd3D}{{8}{18}{Trajectory of XP5 AUV, during the 30\textsuperscript {th} October mission in the \naz Canyon region. The color shading represents the interquartile range (IQD) of temperature values recorded within each model grid cell illustrating the horizontal resolution of the statistical model. Results are shown for three representative depth layers: near-surface, 20 m, and 40 m, capturing distinct vertical regimes. Higher IQD values indicate regions of higher thermal variability within the model grid. Close-up view of the 20 m layer reveal fine-scale fluctuations occurring inside single grid elements illustrating AUVs capture subgrid-scale structure that the model does not resolve.\relax }{figure.caption.14}{}}
